// Syncthing syncs ONLY all.py across machines — it is gitignored (machine-shared
// config that references Bitwarden field names, no secret values). Everything
// else in group_data/ (features.py, raspi.py, raspo.py, all.example.py,
// __pycache__) is tracked in git and distributed that way, so Syncthing must
// stay out of git's path for those. First match wins, top-down: keep all.py,
// ignore the rest.
//
// This file is committed to the repo so every machine gets the same rules;
// Syncthing never syncs .stignore itself.
!all.py
*
